	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It must suck to get raged on like our friend, Molian, huh?  (page 2)  You write this high profile, page long post thinkin', &quot;Yea...  I rock.  I shot that dewd down like a fly.  Now everyone's gonna encourage me and next time I play, maybe that sexy Wood Elf will finally notice me...,&quot; but then you come back to gain your gloating rights and you are greeted with bashing, trashing, and tears.  I'm not sure what I'd do.  I think I'd cry...  Then I'd join a red server.  Molian- I have nothing against you, bud.  Just using you as an example:)  Feel free to rage on me if ya think I'm a f**khead too:)  I'll post another describing the various feelings felt while reading Anti-You posts:)  And so this post wasn't just a complete waste of your time, I'll try to contribute some EQ Info...<BR>
<BR>
Stats as I've learned them through 80 days of playing time...<BR>
<BR>
STR: How much you can carry before your agility is affected (if you're carrying more than twice your strength you're unable to move:)), ATK(how often/how hard you hit)<BR>
<BR>
AGI: How often defensive abilities go off (parry, dodge, reposte, etc), small AC increase<BR>
<BR>
DEX: How often warriors, rogues, and rangers get crits (melee, throwing, bows), how often a weapon procs an effect (haste, Ykesha, Berserker Strength), how often casters regain concentration (heard this is not true anymore), no longer affects dual weilding/double attack:(<BR>
<BR>
CHA: How often spells are resisted, duration of DOTs, prices, faction<BR>
<BR>
INT: I think intelligence is fer, like, smartness er sumthin.  Dunno though.  Might be if yer an idiot er not, though.  Dunno.<BR>
<BR>
WIS: Mana for healing classes (Cleric, Druid, Shaman, Ranger, Paladin: wisdom X level X 0.2), also determines success of trade skill attempts.<BR>
<BR>
STA: Adds a little hp, determines regen/mana regen ability.  If you run out of food/drink, eventually you will run out of stamina, and you will be unable to heal or regain mana naturally.  Stamina goes down on boats but does not affect anything and you don't consume food/drink on boats.  Heavy weapons will bring your stamina right down.  No stamina lowers some stats like str/agi after a while.  Stamina is the most underrated stat in the game in my opinion.<BR>
<BR>
INT: How fast you learn skills (battle/trade skill/ability), mana for pure casters and Shadowknights (Wizard, Magician, Necromancer, Enchanter).<BR>
<BR>
AC: Arguably the most vital stat for warriors along with strength, and extremely important for hybrids (Ranger, Paladin, ShadowKnight), goes up with defense skill level, items with AC, buffs, and agility.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
By the way...  Dirtog is right about the sleeves' location.  (page 2)  It's pretty deep in Middle Guk, on the Azure Lord.  He looks like the Avatar of Fear but blue.  He can double for  95 but doesn't cast.  Got about 5k hp.  His friends are kinda wimps so not a tough break.  He'll drop the arms and legs about even, and the Azure Blade as a rare.  And I mean RARE....    <BR>
Actually this is all BS and you shouldn't listen to me ever again:-P<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
I don't usually talk this much...  Ok, well I do, but the servers are down for a patch so I needed something to do EQ oriented:)  Hehe.  If you've made it this far I hope it hasn't been a complete waste of your time.  I suppose this is a pretty high-profile, page long (or more) post.  The riskiest kind:)  Heh.  I was gonna remain anonymous but I think I'll give some vague identity info...<BR>
<BR>
M A (Myst)<BR>
Ranger<BR>
Brell:)<BR>
<BR>
Lataz, y'all.  Stay real, and remember to leave some time for RL:)  Peace.
